abstract: 2 part compilation of MAP submissions from early days of the project
description: The Memory and Place (MAP) project captures stories, feelings and memories that we attach to places we know. This compile, in two parts, presents some of those stories and excerpts from the MAP Collection project: MAP #1: Brunswick (Froggie's gone), Northcote (Westbourne Grove), Cohuna (Tom Olsson's Cohuna), Kensington (ReLocated - The Venny kids), Collingwood (North), Dunolly (The Posidon rush) MAP #2: Carlton (Lygon Street), Ararat (Memories of Ararat c1930), Preston (Festival of kites), Burnley (Stack)
